A SHOOT-OUT between the police and robbery suspects ensued in the Vereeniging CBD, Vaal on Friday morning, 10 February. This was after four thugs stormed a shop and took an undisclosed amount of money before fleeing the scene. But one suspect surrendered to the police after a shoot-out. Police spokesman Captain Fikile Funda told Daily Sunthat a 30-year-old male suspect has been apprehended following a business robbery on Friday morning in Vereeniging. Funda said it is reported that four armed men stormed a store as the owner was opening for business. While the suspects were still busy in the shop, a passerby witnessed the incident and alerted members of the community. According to Funda, members of the community pursued the suspects who took an undisclosed amount money from the shop and fled in a Nissan Almera car. Community members met cops from the K9 Unit who were patrolling at De Villiers Street and the officers joined the chase. The suspects abandoned their car, fled on foot and started shooting at the cops. Funda said one suspect was arrested while three managed to get away. You need to be SIGNED IN to comment! Police have opened a case for business robbery, attempted murder, and possession of unlicensed firearm and ammunition. The arrested suspect will appear in the Vereeniging Magistrates Court soon. Police are appealing to anyone with information that can lead to the arrest of the three other suspects to call their nearest police station.